message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "EoSAlign: An Open-Source Software for Calculating, Comparing, and Aligning Pressure Under Extreme Conditions"
abstract: "Allison Pease and Heidi N. Krauss contributed equally to this work and share joint first authorship. EoSAlign is a desktop application designed for comparing and converting pressure calibrations using equations of state (EoS). This application enables the comparison of measured data directly with published calibrations of similar composition and methodology. This application supports both measured data and pressure converted data."
doi: 10.5281/zenodo.21230860
date-released: 2026-07-07
license: GPL-3.0-only
repository-code: "https://github.com/EoSApplications/EoSAlign"
url: "https://eosalign.com"
